OL,6,FPrime Minister Rishi Sunak said it was
OL,7,F"a day of shame for the British state"
OL,8,Fafter the Infected Blood Inquiry
OL,9,Fidentified a "catalogue of systemic,
OL,10,Fcollective and individual failures".
OL,12,FNHS England chief executive Amanda
OL,13,FPritchard has issued an apology to
OL,14,Fvictims of the infected blood scandal
OL,15,Fon behalf of the health service in
OL,16,FEngland.
OL,18,FShe said "put their trust in the care
OL,19,Fthey got from the NHS over many years,
OL,20,Fand they were badly let down".
